---
import AboutHeroImage from '../assets/blog-placeholder-about.jpg';
import Layout from '../layouts/BlogPost.astro';
---

<Layout
	title="About Zengarden"
	description="Zengarden helps institutions support student wellbeing with guided insight, human care, and responsible clinical oversight."
	pubDate={new Date('April 14 2026')}
	heroImage={AboutHeroImage}
>
	<p>
		Zengarden is built to help schools and universities create a stronger emotional support layer for
		students. We combine structured self-reflection, guided mentorship, and access to qualified
		psychological professionals so institutions can respond earlier and more responsibly.
	</p>

	<p>
		Our approach is intentionally human-led. Insight tools help students understand themselves,
		mentors provide grounded direction, and clinicians add oversight where care needs become more
		serious. That balance helps institutions scale support without reducing students to dashboards or
		automated labels.
	</p>

	<p>
		Zengarden is designed around privacy, trust, and practical action. We focus on giving schools a
		clearer view of student needs while protecting dignity, supporting informed decisions, and making
		it easier for the right people to step in at the right time.
	</p>

	<p>
		The result is a calmer, more connected support system: students feel seen, institutions gain
		confidence in their processes, and care teams can work with better context instead of reacting too
		late.
	</p>
</Layout>
